* SMC Diode Solutions ST15100S -- 100V 15A Trench-MOS Schottky rectifier (TO-277B)
* Datasheet N2219 Rev.- (no vendor SPICE model published; this is a datasheet fit).
*
* Derived by curve-fitting the datasheet (Fugu2/dcdc-tools spice-fit/), and
* cross-checked against SMC's own model for the sibling ST15100 (same die family,
* TO-220AC): N=1.03, RS=0.0151, BV=120, CJO=2.04n, TT=0 -- this fit lands in that
* family. At 25C the sibling matches ST15100S well (VF@15A 0.666, CT 616/446pF).
* BUT the sibling's temperature block is unphysical: EG=1.17 (Si bandgap) + large
* TRS1/TRS2 make its forward VF@15A *rise* to 0.863V at 125C -- which contradicts
* SMC's OWN ST15100 datasheet (N1038: VF@15A 0.70->0.66 over 25->125C) by +203mV and
* the wrong direction. This fit uses EG=0.69 (real Schottky barrier, pinned by the
* reverse-leakage 750x temp ratio) so VF correctly *falls* with temp and matches the
* ST15100S table. (Note: both siblings' Fig1 curves have the same shape -- 125C stays
* lower-VF, no crossover, gap widening at high current -- which no physical single
* diode can trace, so the fit is anchored to the table VF@15A, not the chart tail.)
*
* VALIDATED in LTspice (spice-fit/val_fwd.cir, val_cap.cir):
*   Forward VF @15A : 25C = 0.685 V (datasheet typ 0.68 / max 0.71)
*                    125C = 0.598 V (datasheet typ 0.60 / max 0.64)
*   Junction cap CT : 2200 / 663 / 436 pF @ 0 / 5 / 10 V  (datasheet 2200 / 650 / 420)
*                     CT @5V,1MHz = 663 pF (datasheet 650 pF typ)
* Fit is optimised for the 10-20A operating region; the 2A and 40A tails carry
* larger error (a single SPICE diode cannot match the full 2-40A span, which
* diverges with temperature, at both 25C and 125C simultaneously).
*
* EG=0.69 (Schottky barrier height) is pinned by the datasheet reverse-leakage
* temperature ratio (0.01->7.5mA, 25->125C) AND reproduces the forward VF(T) shift.
* TT=0: Schottky, negligible minority-carrier reverse recovery.
* CAVEAT: reverse-leakage MAGNITUDE is under-modelled (~0.5uA vs 10uA typ @100V),
* a known limitation of the single-diode Schottky model; the temperature *behaviour*
* is physical. Reverse leakage is negligible for switching/conduction simulation.
*
.MODEL ST15100S D (
+ LEVEL=1 IS=5e-7 N=1.05 RS=0.0144
+ BV=120 IBV=1e-4
+ CJO=2.2n VJ=1.1 MJ=0.7 FC=0.5
+ TT=0 EG=0.69 XTI=1.3 TRS1=0 )
